50|$|In 1866, the big <b>church</b> <b>bell</b> of Aguilar arrived. Fr. Agustin Gallego {{received}} it {{in behalf of}} the parish. In 1877, another <b>church</b> <b>bell</b> was bought while another <b>church</b> <b>bell</b> was repaired. This was {{during the time of}} Fr. Victoriano Garcia Ciano.|$|R
50|$|The <b>church's</b> <b>bell</b> tolled 29 {{times in}} November 1975 to mourn {{the loss of}} the {{freighter}} Edmund Fitzgerald; once for each of her 29 crew members. The church continued to hold an annual memorial, reading the names of the crewmen and ringing the <b>church</b> <b>bell</b> until 2006.|$|R
