50|$|A {{few decades}} ago, {{commodities}} weighed {{in terms of}} long hundredweight included cattle, cattle fodder, fertilizers, coal, some industrial chemicals, other industrial materials, and so on. However, since increasing metrication in most English-speaking countries, it is now less used. <b>Church</b> <b>bell</b> ringers use the unit commonly, although <b>church</b> <b>bell</b> manufacturers are increasingly moving over to the metric system.|$|R
